DTSTART:20260603T180000Z
DTEND:20260603T203000Z
SUMMARY:Joe Turner's Come and Gone
LOCATION:Barrymore Theatre, 243 West 47th Street, New York NY 10036
DESCRIPTION:<p>Golden Globe&reg; winner Taraji P. Henson (<em>The Color
  Purple</em>) makes her Broadway debut opposite Cedric the Entertainer
  (<em>The Neighborhood</em>), returning to the stage in a luminous revival
  of August Wilson&rsquo;s<em> Joe Turner&rsquo;s Come and Gone</em>.<br
  /><br />Seth and Bertha Holly (Cedric and Henson) keep a warm, orderly
  home for those navigating uncertain paths. But when a mysterious man named
  Herald Loomis arrives with his young daughter, the stillness of the house
  begins to shift. As his past slowly unravels, long-buried truths come to
  light&mdash;and everyone within the house is called to reckon with the
  meaning of freedom, identity, and belonging.<br /><br />Directed by
  Emmy&reg; and Golden Globe winner Debbie Allen (<em>Cat on a Hot Tin
  Roof</em>) and also starring Tony Award&reg; nominee Joshua Boone
  (<em>Skeleton Crew</em>, <em>The Outsiders</em>) and Tony Award winner
  Ruben Santiago-Hudson (<em>Lackawanna Blues</em>), this timeless American
  classic is set in a Pittsburgh boardinghouse in 1911, during a pivotal era
  of migration and transformation. As people move in search of opportunity
  and renewal, they carry with them untold stories&mdash;of loss,
  resilience, and hope.<br /><br />Described by<em> The New York Times</em>
  as &ldquo;a drama of indisputable greatness,&rdquo; <em>Joe Turner&rsquo;s
  Come and Gone</em> is a profoundly moving story of personal awakening,
  collective memory, and the quiet power of human connection&mdash;brought
  vividly to life by an extraordinary creative team.</p>
END:VEVENT
